project title: Customer Churn Prediction
Customer Churn Prediction
📝 Abstract

Customer churn prediction is a machine learning project designed to identify customers who are likely to discontinue a company’s service. By analyzing historical customer data such as demographics, account details, and service usage patterns, the system builds predictive models to detect churn behavior.

The project applies data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), feature engineering, and classification algorithms to generate accurate predictions. The insights derived from this model help businesses reduce revenue loss and improve customer retention strategies.

🎯 Main Goal

The primary goal of this project is to:

Predict whether a customer will churn or not.

Identify key factors influencing customer churn.

Help businesses take proactive steps to retain high-risk customers.

Improve customer satisfaction and reduce financial loss.

🔍 Features

📊 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to understand customer behavior.

🧹 Data Cleaning & Preprocessing (handling missing values, encoding categorical variables, scaling).

🏗️ Feature Engineering to improve model performance.

🤖 Multiple Machine Learning Models (Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest, etc.).

📈 Model Evaluation using Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score, and ROC-AUC.

🔎 Feature Importance Analysis to determine key churn indicators.

📉 Visualization Dashboards for better data interpretation.

